cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper deals with detecting attacks on highly privileged software using cryptographic signatures and proposes a behavior monitoring approach to detect attacks at runtime. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses instrumenting code executed on the main CPU to send information about its behavior to the monitor, which involves software engineering techniques. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with detecting attacks on a system management mode and proposes a co-processor based approach to monitor the behavior of the main CPU. 
- cs.AR (Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses the behavior of the x86 architecture and its execution modes. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on programming languages, but it does discuss instrumenting code executed on the main CPU, which involves programming techniques.
